You have found out that the sun works on the same principles as other stars: It was found out that the activity of all stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation and nothing else.
To determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow, the luminosity and the rotation are taken into account together.
The smaller the Rossby number is, the less active the star is in terms of flipping the magnetic field.
