The 802.11n standard runs on the frequencies 2,4 Ghz and 5,0 Ghz.
It can be backward-compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g, provided that the base station has Dual-Radio.
The speed of 802.11 n is significantly faster than that of its predecessors, which had a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbit/s.
